President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to later address the nation following the meetings. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on COVID-19 at 19:30 on Monday. Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu confirmed the official time of the address in Pretoria. On Sunday, the president met with ministers and business about the effects of coronavirus on our country. WATCH: Ramaphosa, party leaders address nation As the number of COVID-19 cases rise in South Africa, government is stepping up efforts to enforce the state of national disaster. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.